{
  "text": "The severity of histologic lesions was assed using a score (HIS) that was based on six parameters: intra-alveolar edema, hyaline membrane formation, hemorrhage, recruitment of granulocytes into the air space, focal alveolar collapse or consolidation, and epithelial desquamation/necrosis of airways or alveoli. Each parameter was evaluated semiquantitatively using the following scale: 0 = absent, 1 = mild, 2 = moderate, and 3 = prominent. In addition, the percentage of the involved area of each histologic specimen was estimated (0 to 100%) to quantify any observed histologic changes [CITATION_1] .",
